President Jacob Zuma and his son have been named on the hit-list of the Anti-State Capture Death Squad Alliance for possible assassination.Sources have revealed to ANN7 that Zuma&#8217;s name appears alongside that of former Eskom CEO and member of parliament Brian Molefe and all the Gupta brothers on the hit list.*BREAKING* #StateCapture Sources reveal that President Zuma, his son, Brian Molefe, Ben Ngubane, Gupta brothers names are on the hit list. Kalden O Lachungpa (@KaldenOngmu) April 27, 2017Eskom board chairman Ben Ngubane&#8217;s name also appears on the hit-list. The identity of Zuma&#8217;s son who appears on the hit list has yet to be confirmed.The revelation of the names comes after the Hawks on Wednesday arrested a 23 year old man for allegedly plotting to assassinate up to 19 cabinet ministers.The Hawks arrested the suspect in Midrand, Johannesburg while he was explaining to a number of donors how the assassination of state capture beneficiaries was going to be carried out.The 23 year-old male suspect is believed to be the leader of two organisations, the Anti-State Capture Death Squad Alliance and the Anti-White Monopoly Capitalist Regime which have been implicated in the plot to assassinate South Africans who were implicated in former Public Protector Thuli Madonsela s State capture report.The suspect is expected to appear in court on Friday to face charges of conspiracy to commit murder.-TNA Reporter